    // FAQ
    "faq.label": "FAQ",
    "faq.title": "Questions? We've got answers.",
    "faq.subtitle": "Everything you might want to know before downloading.",
    "faq.q1": "Do I need a Home Assistant server to use HAHome?",
    "faq.a1": 'Yes — HAHome is a client app for <a href="https://www.home-assistant.io" style="color:var(--accent);">Home Assistant</a>, the open-source home automation platform. You\'ll need a running Home Assistant instance (on a Raspberry Pi, NAS, Home Assistant Green, or any server) that is reachable from your device. HAHome connects to it via your local network or a remote URL.',
    "faq.q2": "Is HAHome affiliated with the official Home Assistant project?",
    "faq.a2": "No. HAHome is an independent, third-party app. It uses Home Assistant's open REST and WebSocket APIs but is not made by or affiliated with Nabu Casa or the Home Assistant project.",
    "faq.q3": "What devices and platforms does HAHome run on?",
    "faq.a3": "HAHome runs on iPhone and Mac (iOS 26.2+ and macOS 26.2+). One purchase covers both platforms. iOS widgets are also available for quick light control from your Home Screen.",
    "faq.q4": "How does HAHome connect to my Home Assistant?",
    "faq.a4": "HAHome uses OAuth to log you in securely via your browser. After login, it maintains a WebSocket connection for real-time state updates and uses the Home Assistant REST API to send commands. Your credentials are stored in the iOS Keychain — never in a third-party server.",
    "faq.q5": "What's the difference between the free version and HAHome Pro?",
    "faq.a5": "The free version lets you control up to 10 lights, 5 climate devices, 5 covers, 5 media players, 5 switches and 5 automations. Security cameras and energy monitoring are always unlimited. <strong>HAHome Pro ($4.99, one-time)</strong> removes all entity limits, unlocks 13 exclusive app themes, 52 premium light icons, the ability to reorder home tiles, layout sharing with up to 9 people, and state history for any entity (1, 2, 3 or 7 days).",
    "faq.q6": "Does HAHome support Family Sharing?",
    "faq.a6": "Yes. HAHome Pro is a family-shareable in-app purchase, so one purchase unlocks Pro for everyone in your Apple Family Sharing group.",
    "faq.q7": "How does layout sharing work?",
    "faq.a7": "With HAHome Pro, you can create named groups and generate encrypted invite links (up to 9 people). Each invitee gets a personalised layout — you choose exactly which entities they can see. They open the invite link on their device and import your home in seconds.",
    "faq.q8": "Does HAHome work remotely, outside my home network?",
    "faq.a8": "Yes, as long as your Home Assistant is accessible remotely. This can be done via Home Assistant Cloud (Nabu Casa), a reverse proxy, or a VPN. HAHome simply connects to whatever URL you provide — local or remote.",
    "faq.q9": "Which Home Assistant entity types are supported?",
    "faq.a9": "HAHome supports lights, climate (HVAC, fans, temperature &amp; humidity sensors), covers (blinds, shutters, garage doors), media players, remotes, switches, fans, security (cameras, door/window/motion/smoke sensors, alarm panels), automations, scenes, scripts, and energy sensors (solar, grid, battery, gas, water). More entity types may be added in future updates.",
    "faq.q10": "Does HAHome send any data to external servers?",
    "faq.a10": "No. HAHome communicates exclusively with your Home Assistant server. No analytics, no telemetry, no third-party services. Your home data stays between your device and your server.",
    "faq.q11": "What is Apple Intelligence and which devices support it?",
    "faq.a11": "Apple Intelligence is Apple\u0027s on-device AI framework. HAHome uses it for Energy Insights (free), Automation Explainer (free), and the \"Ask About Your Home\" conversation mode (Pro). It requires a supported iPhone (iPhone 15 Pro or later) or Mac (M1 or later) with Apple Intelligence enabled in Settings. All AI processing happens entirely on your device — no data is sent to any cloud service.",
    "faq.q12": "Is HAHome accessible for users with disabilities?",
    "faq.a12": "Yes. HAHome is built with full VoiceOver support, Dynamic Type for adjustable text sizes, Voice Control compatibility, and a dark interface with sufficient contrast ratios. Status indicators use both colour and icons to ensure information is never conveyed by colour alone.",

