    "support.bug.cta": "Send bug report",
    "support.common": "Common questions",
    "support.q1": "HAHome can't connect to my Home Assistant",
    "support.a1": "Make sure your Home Assistant URL is correct and reachable from your device. Try opening the URL in Safari first — if it loads, HAHome should be able to connect. If you're connecting remotely, ensure your reverse proxy, Nabu Casa, or VPN is active. Check that your Home Assistant instance is running and not in maintenance mode.",
    "support.q2": "My entities aren't showing up",
    "support.a2": "Make sure the entities are not hidden or disabled in your Home Assistant instance. Try force-closing the app and reopening it to resync with your server. Free tier limits (10 lights, 5 climate, etc.) may also apply — upgrade to Pro to remove all caps.",
    "support.q3": "How do I restore my Pro purchase?",
    "support.a3": "Go to Settings → HAHome Pro → Restore Purchase. Make sure you're signed in with the same Apple ID used for the original purchase. If you purchased through Family Sharing, ensure Family Sharing is enabled in your Apple ID settings.",
    "support.q4": "The app is showing stale / outdated states",
    "support.a4": "HAHome uses a WebSocket connection for live updates. If states appear stale, the connection may have dropped. Force-close the app and reopen it to re-establish the WebSocket connection. Check that your Home Assistant instance is responsive.",
    "support.q5": "How do I delete my account / data?",
    "support.a5": "HAHome doesn't store any personal data on external servers — everything lives on your device and your own Home Assistant. To remove all app data, go to Settings → Sign Out, then delete the app from your device. This removes the stored access token from the iOS Keychain and all local app data.",

    // Privacy page
    "privacy.label": "Legal",
    "privacy.title": "Privacy Policy",
    "privacy.updated": "Last updated: March 2026",
    "privacy.overview.title": "Overview",
    "privacy.overview.desc": "HAHome is designed with privacy at its core. The app communicates exclusively with your own Home Assistant server. We do not operate any backend servers, collect personal data, or track your usage in any way.",
